The fall issue of FEMINIST STUDIES (23.3) is in the mail!

This last issue of our twenty-fifth anniversary year
features two clusters of articles: NATION AND RACE,
SEX AND WORK and GENDER AND SEXUAL IDENTITY IN THE PUBLIC
SPHERE.

NATION AND RACE, SEX AND WORK includes studies which explore
Politics of Prostitution in Ponce, Puerto Rico, 1890-1900;
White Women and Colonialism in Nineteenth-Century British
Columbia; Gender, Family, and Working Class Politics in
India; and Gendered Meanings Under Production in Mexico's
Export Processing Industry.

Our second cluster of articles,  GENDER AND SEXUAL
IDENTITY IN THE PUBLIC SPHERE, explore the International
Women's Movement in the Early Twentieth Century; the
politics of the production of knowledge about breast
cancer; a review essay that exposes the myth of the rich
gay community; and an art essay that examines issues of
sexuality and identity in relation to aging.

And, as in every issue, FEMINIST STUDIES brings both new
and familiar creative voices to our readers.

Stop by our website for the complete table of content for
the issue. www.inform.umd.edu/FemStud

Our plans for the next publishing year promise to be
equally exciting. Our spring issue begins with a cluster of
articles that look at feminism, activism, and the recent
cuts to welfare; our summer issue is devoted exclusively to
issues-- theoretical, practical, and pedagogical--
surrounding doctoral programs in women's studies; and in
the fall, we end the year with a cluster of articles that
examine masculinities.

Subscriptions per volume year are $30.00 for individuals and
$85.00 for institutions. We also offer a student rate of
$20.00 per year (a photocopy of a dated proof of student
status is required in order to receive this rate.) Single
issues are $12.00 each.

You can e-mail your order to femstud@umail.umd.edu. (Be
sure to include your credit card type, number, and
expiration date.)

You can also order via snail mail with either a credit card
or a check. Send the appropriate information to Feminist
Studies, c/o Women's Studies Department, Woods Hall,
University of Maryland, College Park, Maryland 20742.
Or visit our website and print the subscription form.





 ----------------------
 Mary-Jo Povisil
 mp57@umail.umd.edu
