>> I have rarely seen accounts about birthing or midwifery in
>> women's studies.
There is an excellent case study of midwifery at the Rotunda
hospital in Dublin by Jo Murphy-Lawless in the *Irish Women's STudies
REader* ed. by Ailbhe Smyth (Dublin: Attic Press, 1993) pp.9-19
The article is called 'The Silencing of Women in Childbirth or
Let's Hear it for Bartholomew and the boys'.

Siobhan Holland
