Date:         Fri, 5 Dec 1997 13:43:18 EST
Reply-To:     Women's Studies List <WMST-L@UMDD.UMD.EDU>
Sender:       Women's Studies List <WMST-L@UMDD.UMD.EDU>
From:         Jenny Lloyd <JLLOYD@ACSPR1.ACS.BROCKPORT.EDU>
Subject:      Re: WMST L: Re: birthing and midwifery

With reference to Ehrenreich and English's book on midwives and witches,
historians (including women's and gender historians) agree that the is
no firm evidence that midwives were singled out in the European witch
hunt, so its thesis needs to be nuanced.  There is a wealth of scholarship
on the witch hunt itself.
You might look at Jessica Mitford, The American Way of Birth (Penguin,
1992) for a recent history of midwifery in the US.
Jenny Lloyd
SUNY at Brockport
jlloyd@acspr1.acs.brockport.edu
