I don't know about the journals, but just about every tech-writing book
I've looked at in the past few years now has a section on gender-neutral
language.  They may not yet all believe it's important in and of itself,
but the threat of sexual harassment lawsuits is enough to have it included
in the advice to newly-professional writers.  If it's not changed yet (and
now you've got me itching to go open up a couple of business journals even
though they're not my field!), change seems to be coming along.

shelley

