Hey, folks:

    I'm an adjunct at Georgetown and order books for my class through the
local women's bookstore downtown.  It's a great way to expose Women's
Studies majors to feminist community-based enterprise.

    Do other folks do this?  The superstores are killing the small bookstores,
and even my little course makes a big difference for the DC store.

    Best,

    Jaime
