I'm interested to know how this film is used in women's studies courses.
I love the film, saw it in a visual anthropology course years ago, and
have referred to it numerous times in conversations with colleagues, but
it is not well known.  I have thought about using the film to stimulate
discussion of issues around gender and generation and biography.  Any
other ideas?

