Wm. W. Pendleton asks:  ". . .to what extent should we compel students to
by from one source, even when we regard the experience as valuable."

I'm sorry, but don't a majority of professors indirectly *compel* their
students to buy from the campus bookstore and/or those close to the campus
by virtue of providing those stores with advance notice of what texts they
will be using for the coming semester?

He further adds: "If I pick a favorite cause and compel students to support
it, is not everyone free to do the same?"

The issue here, as I see it, is not about supporting a "cause", but about
supporting a community resource.

Dra. Angela Pattatucci
Universidad de Puerto Rico
a_pattatucci@upr1.upr.clu.edu
