I am seeking ideas for novels written by women who live outside the U.S.
and who address issues of race, ethnicity, class, and/or sexual
identity--in addition to gender--in their work. I hope to assign such a
novel in an undergraduate course about global perspectives on women. My
hope is to provide students with more multi-dimensional understandings of
women's lived experiences than would be provided by other types of
textbooks.

If you have suggestions or have used novels of this type in your courses,
I'd appreciate hearing from you. Please respond privately to
LLP@cnsvax.albany.edu

Thank you,

