Hi everyone -- I'm trying to think of the name of the movie that came out
a year or two ago, foreign language film, a sort of cynical follow-up to
"A Question of Silence" (by the same film maker), about a woman who
returns, with her adult daughter, to her home village just as her mother
is dying.  I say it is a cynical follow-up because the woman who made the
both films said that the second one was basically an expression of her
giving up on the possibility of radical change.

So, can anybody out there name that movie?  I'm trying to give the title
to someone else to possibly include in a course, and it is driving me nuts.

Thanks for any help!

Joyce Altobelli
Cornell University
jga2@cornell.edu
