I find myself agreeing with Daphne Patai on this one: sloppy research does
nobody any good. Generalizations are deadly.
But while I believe that rape is a power&control, not a sex thing, and
this goes for rapists of any gender and orientation, I frankly have a hard
time extrapolating from prison rape to (for lack of a better term) in-the-
community rape.
And I have an even harder time accepting "rape" and "battering" as
synonymous--again, no matter what the gender and orientation of those
involved.
Once we get the terminology down, maybe we can proceed with the
methodology...

