I don't mean to single Stacey out, but I just wanted to let the entire
list know that my original query was for books, articles, videos,
brochures, etc. that addressed the issue of lesbians who are raped by other
lesbians.  The therapist at the local rape crisis center asked me for
materials that might help a client who has been in this situation, a
lesbian acquaintance rape.  I didn't mean for this to turn into a
discussion of statistics, samples, etc.  I also noted that the therapist
and I have all the resources on lesbian relationship violence that we
needed.  The rape in question did not take place in a relationship
context.

Moreover, (re: Daphne Patai's post) anyone who would suggest that lesbians
or gay men cannot/do not rape is just not in touch with the research and
the information gathered at rape crisis centers, etc.

I am gathering from the paucity of resources that lesbian-on-lesbian rape
(for lack of a better term) is an unexplored area of study/resource
building. This would be a fruitful area for new research. Am I wrong?

Thanks to everyone who has replied.

