Subject:      Re: rape and power (was rape and prison)
Comments: To: Kelley Crouse <kcwalker@SYR.EDU>
In-Reply-To:  <199712180151.UAA11005@syr.edu>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: TEXT/PLAIN; charset=US-ASCII

I appreciate the distinction made here about the difference between
sexuality/rape and power/domination.  It seems important to call rape in
any situation a need to dominate, manipulate, and control, and to reclaim
the term power for what it really means -- to have ability, potential.
As long as we continue to interchange the terms power with control/
dominance/ and manipulation, we will never be able to claim fully our own
power or appreciate fully the potential of others.

Peace,  Jacqueline Haessly   jacpeace@acs.stritch.edu   Image Peace!




