One of my mentors, Judy Long, used to have us do research on women
scholars who'd been marginalized or completely left out of the
'canon' in sociology.  It was a really terrific project, eye
opening even as a jaded grad student.  So I want to do a variation
of this in my Intro Women's Studies course.  Judy called these
women our 'feminist foremothers' even though they may not have
labeled themselves feminists or conceived of their work as feminist.
 I'm largely familiar with only names associated with sociology and
social theory.  So I was hoping that I could solicit names  of women
in other disciplines.

Thanks for your help.

Kelley
