Subject:      Film Article Added

A couple of months ago I placed an article that I had written about
ways in which three feminist filmmakers depict violence against women in
their films.  It's FILM ART001 on the WMST-L's FILM FILELIST.

I've just added a second article titled "Women in Hollywood Films of the '90s:
The Age of Comeuppance."  This piece was written for a trinational conference
on The North American Woman in the 1990s held in Mexico City in October, 1996.
There were other papers on women in film in the 1990s by Canadian and Mexican
authors.  In this piece I try to extend Molly Haskell's practice of character-
izing each decade, as she did in From Reverence to Rape.  Since that book
ends with the late 1980s, I look back over the reviews I've done for "Women
and Film" on "The Women's Show" since 1990 and try to do the same for this
decade.

You may get a copy of this article just the same way you get a film review:

Send the command GET FILM ART002 FILM to  LISTSERV@umdd.umd.edu.

Linda Lopez McAlister


